The inner city of Joburg has been plunged into darkness for the past 12 hours following a group of thieves digging into underground cables just after midnight, burning the cables to get to the copper.
According to City Power spokesman Sol Masolo, currently the tunnels are toxic with fumes and smoke and inaccessible to technicians.
“City Power has requested environmental and safety experts to assess the situation and determine if it is safe for our electricians and technicians to enter the tunnels for work purposes. After the environmental assessors have concluded their safety tests, our technicians will conduct electrical tests on all cables and start with the repair process,” he said.
 The areas that have been affected by the power interruption include:   City Power will keep customers updated via its twitter handle: @CityPowerjhb. City Power has apologised to customers affected by outage for the inconvenience caused.